#Text=NFL : Cowboys cornerback Pacman Jones ca n't discuss police incident
#Text=Saturday , October 11 , 2008

#Text=Dallas Cowboys cornerback Adam " Pacman " Jones was not available to speak with reporters Thursday after a Tuesday night incident involving Jones and a bodyguard in a hotel bathroom in the south-Central American city of Dallas , Texas .
#Text=Officials are calling the incident private and said charges are not likely to be filed .
#Text=As of Thursday , the Cowboys have not disciplined Jones .
#Text=Police were notified by hotel staff after workers heard a disturbance in the hotel lobby men 's bathroom where Jones and his bodyguard arguing .
#Text=Jones and his bodyguard told police everything was fine and were driven away by a friend .

#Text=Cowboys owner Jerry Jones spoke with members of the media on Thursday , saying that he was " very disappointed in that we 're having to deal with this , " saying that the altercation was not a big deal .
#Text=" They were literally kidding each other , " Jerry Jones told the Associated Press on Thursday .
#Text=" They were jiving around ... and all of a sudden one of them starting saying some things , and here you go . "
#Text=Cowboys nose tackle Tank Johnson said everything was overblown and should n't distract the team .
#Text=" This is not that big of a deal , " Johnson told the Associated Press .
#Text=" Nobody 's in jail , nobody 's in trouble , nobody 's hurt .
